To give more information regarding the reason for revert, 
1) the PR failed some tests that were run by TAP presubmit, but not by kokoro tests.
2) We have another copy of ALTS code in net/grpc, which causes a conflict (e.g., function redefinition) with the ATLS code to be imported. Our original plan was to delete the internal version once the github version safely landed in Google3, which obviously does not work out. 

I will create a new PR that contains all the changes in the reverted PR together with the fixes for the 1st issue, then prepare for an import patch to resolve the 2nd issue.
Checked with @matt-kwong  and looks like the bazel failures are known issues.
